Honestly can’t beat Komorebi. I’m a pretty simple sashimi purist everywhere else but the signature rolls here are everything 💦 if you don’t order the OCEAN VINAIGRETTE then gtfo. It’s a perfect roll. Chef Eric’s sauce work is insane, each one unique and perfectly balanced. dude consistantly sneaks the right amount of acidity into each dish where you’d least expect it - see blueberry ponzu vinaigrette in the aforementioned roll or mango in the “tropical.” 10/10 service. The freshest sushi in Chicago, IL. Parking is convenient and no hassles. It's not a trendy spot but if you want fresh sushi at a Resturant that has a high turnover (ideal) in world of sushi then drive to Sushi Gen. Thinking about it makes my mouth water!

Probably the best sushi place in the Wicker Park area. Large tables can accommodate a large group, and they have smaller more intimate tables up front. Get the flaming sushi--its great for a fun photo (and tastes good!)

I think the food was excellent. The decor is modern Asian themed with plants in vases. The wait staff were courteous.
Favorite sushi spot in wicker park. Lovely cozy interior. More importantly the food here is great. They have simple tastey rolls, and if you like spicy soups, they have the best spicy miso soup.
This is our favorite sushi place! $17 for 3 rolls and a soup or salad! And the fish is so fresh and I love the simplicity of the rolls! The staff is so kind and fun and its BYOB!

The food, atmosphere, and staff was superb! Had the spicy miso soup, shrimp tempura, cucumber roll, and edamame. All of the dishes were very fresh and delicious. I left feeling quite satisfied after my meal.

My boyfriend and I came here for dinner on a Thursday. The service and ambiance were great. They were busy but not packed. They have cute Halloween decorations up currently. We ordered miso soup, mafia roll, tropical roll, and sashimi appetizer sampler. Also, the extotic bomba for dessert. The miso soup was wonderful--it was perfectly salty and liked the addition of mushroom in the soup. We liked both rolls and the sashimi tasted fresh. The only fish I did not like personally in the sashimi sampler was the  sea bass. The dessert was good, but nothing amazing. This restaurant is BYOB.

Komorebi Sushi is delicious! They do sushi right. The presentation is beautiful and the sushi is just perfect. The rolls are made and cut to size appropriately too so you're not trying to figure out how to get the whole thing in your mouth either. One of my favorite aspects of this restaurant though is their selection of veggie rolls. While they have the traditional avocado and sweet potato rolls that you see at most sushi restaurants, they also have 5 or 6 special veggie rolls that are much more intricate (and tasty). Highly recommend!!

The sushi here is excellent. The rice is cooked perfectly and is provided in the right proportion to the fish. The nigiri is appropriately sized so that you aren't chewing forever. I loved the ginger salad and the shumai. Can't beat BYOB either. Excellent value all around.

Wow what a treat. I was stuck just on their appetizers as they were breathtakingly beautiful in the plating and the food tasted outstanding. Really fun rolls, great execution and the fish was outstanding for the price. It's BYOB so bring a good bottle of róse or a Torrontés. This is one of my favorite spots on Milwaukee and a new "must come back" spot.  Didn't make it to dessert but I had my eye on their version of cheese cake.

Kind of expensive, but really good quality, fast and kind service, and a nice atmosphere. The window seats are nice when they open the windows. All of the presentation is beautiful, one of our rolls came on fire!! We got the Turtle (shown), Atlantic (pretty good, but it had lots of salad greens in it that I didn’t particularly like), Red Dragon and Sunset. Would definitely go back!
Have yet to try anything I didn't like!

Possibly the best sushimi I've ever had. We ordered the Sushi Surpreme, which was a great price. The service was great, and I will definitely be visiting again.

So the clothes upstairs are higher end brands, but still Obey shirts are about ninety bucks. They have hats, jackets, shirts, sweaters, winter coats, bomber jackets, rain coats. Both men's and women's clothes and shoes.  Downstairs is where all the army surplus stuff is at. I was looking for a wool or acrylic commando sweater. They had those and some shawl neck ones for about $49-66. But I also found some more pain sweaters for $18. They have a lot of clothes downstairs, and boots and accessories and jackets that are no-one name and very much less expensive. I ended up getting two sweaters and a wool hat and contemplated getting a balaclava or a neoprene face mask / gaiter

This BYOB sushi place is great. Friendly staff, giant menu full of creative rolls, and delicious food. If you are looking for a photo op, order the fire roll for a fun surprise. ;)

Amazing, creative sushi and BYOB - will definitely be back.
Great sushi and great atmosphere.  Servers were very friendly and I love that it is BYOB. I will definitely be back for more!
Amazing food. Very fresh. Ask for the chef's special dish of the day; it won't disappoint.
Amazing food and service. BYOB on top of that
BYOB. Great sushi and service!
The sushi was so fresh and delicious.  The atmosphere was also really nice and cute!

Omg this place is amazing. The decor is really cool. Lots of big comfy seats, lots of candles, very comfortable. The food is absolutely spectacular. Each dish was better than the last. Strongly recommend this place to everyone. Good mix of classic and special rolls.

Totally digging this place!  The food Got the following:  Crispy tuna Couple next to me was not a fan of this but I really liked it. I love the crunch of the rice and the really good tuna. Also super easy to eat with your hands! Love it.  Smoky Hamachi Meh - Couple next to me recommended it and honestly it was more show than anything. Sure it's cool to see the smoke but seriously not worth it. I would not get this.  Spicy Tuna Roll #2 favorite. So everyone has a spicy tuna roll but something about this was just awesome! I am still thinking about this alone and will be the primary factor I will be coming back! Fantastic balance of flavors and textures.  Salmon Roll Why oh why do sushi places lately decided putting a lemon on a roll is a great idea? I hate it! I feel it takes away from the taste of the fish and way to overpowering. Not a huge fan of salmon either but I tried one piece and I was done.  Kurogoma If only this was served everywhere!! I love black sesame ice cream and this was fantastic!! The crunchy pieces combined with the rest of the dessert was simply fantastic! The highlight of the night!  The ambience A few large tables and really meant for group gatherings but you quickly make friends with people sitting next to you. Super romantic with the dark lighting and I believe it's a BYOB!  The service Super quick and friendly. Even made room for us at last minute on a Friday night. Will be coming back for sure!
What a spot!! Been looking for a quality sushi spot in Chicago for a whole and this is the one. Good eclectic offerings with quality fish.

Good food, the spicy miso soup and spicy garlic edamame were nice twists to our standard sushi-night fare. Friendly service. BYOB, which is nice considering there's the Jewel right across Milwaukee Ave.
Everything was delicious and the way they plate their food is gorgeous.

Komorebi is one of our favorite sushi places in Chicago!  The menu is inventive, the quality of food is excellent, and the price-value is reasonable.  Thanks to Eric and Minnie for bringing an excellent new restaurant to the Wicker Park area!
The spicy miso soup is a must! Sushi is delicious.
